Nice predictions, I agree with most of those except:

I can't see Gone Girl or Inherent Vice being Oscar standard or even 
Imitation Game just doesn't look down their alley. I haven't heard of 
Knights of Cups, there doesn't seem to be much about it, however I don't 
think that director can ride on Tree of Life all his life (ha). I agree 
Unbroken will win Best Film, but I actually think Nolan will take away his 
first award for Directing. Steve Carell will definitely nab Best Actor, 
though I think Nicole Kidman's role will be a flop, I think that's a no, 
this might be the year Amy Adams finally takes one. I also think Christoph 
Waltz will get a nom (Though I don't know if that counts as Lead or 
supporting) and Tim Burton will get a nom.

FYI, if you're looking for more films to consider for predictions. There's 
a film called Blackbird coming out later this year starring Gugu 
Mbatha-Raw, she looks like she's taking on a few roles in hopes of an Oscar 
and something about this film rings dark horse even with little info, and 
one that will definitely get a nomination is Boyhood, the Richard Linklater 
film that was filmed over the course of 12 years with the actor actually 
growing up with the character.﻿
